{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}
'''Oldisleben I''' is an [[archeological]] site of the [[Eemian]] [[interglacial period]] located north of [[Weimar]] in the [[Oldisleben]] municipality, [[Germany]]. Findings at the site include some of the earliest known engravings on portable objects of bone, ivory and stone, dating back between 135,000 and 80,000 [[Before Present|BP]].
